[2] Cholera - Zambia (Lusaka)
Date: Tue 10 Oct 2017
Source: AllAfrica, Zambia Reports [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201710100747.html


Lusaka has been hit by a cholera outbreak with merely the 1st signs of rain. The number of cholera cases have reached 17 with 2 more cases reported in Lusaka's Kanyama Township. Cholera in Zambia is an annual problem although the public may be concerned that with barely the rain season commencing the capital city has already fallen.

The patients are admitted at the Kanyama Cholera Centre with the disease having broken out on 4 Oct 2017. The affected are Chipata, Mazyopa, Kabanana, and Kanyama Townships.

[Byline: George Mwenya]

--
